The Herald Condolence message by the First Lady of Zimbabwe Amai Auxillia Mnangagwa following the death of four staff members in a road accident in Nyanga on 24 February 2022 ********** The tragic accident which claimed the lives of my four staff members is a big loss to my office and the nation as a whole. The staff members, whose commitment to duty was exceptional, were part of a dedicated team which played a pivotal role in assisting my office to realise its goals. As a mother, I am deeply saddened by the untimely death of my children. I would like to express my deepest condolences to the bereaved families. I pray that they will find comfort in the knowledge that their loved ones passed away while serving the nation. May their souls rest in eternal peace.